        <name>RZ_GPIO_IOLH_SHIFT</name>
        <initializer>8U</initializer>
        <briefdescription>
<para>RZ/A,G,V-specific GPIO Flags The pin driving ability flags are encoded in the 8 upper bits of <ref refid="group__gpio__interface_1gad435719dccdc37c05852960a7218fbd2" kindref="member">gpio_dt_flags_t</ref> as follows: </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Bit 8..9: Pin driving ability value</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Bit 10: Digital Noise Filter ON/OFF</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Bit 11..12: Digital Noise Filter Number value</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Bit 13..14: Digital Noise Filter Clock Selection value example: gpio-consumer { out-gpios = &lt;&amp;port8 2 (GPIO_PULL_UP | <ref refid="renesas-rz-gpio_8h_1aa905a388dc0ca8b9c532620be7029b8e" kindref="member">RZ_GPIO_FILTER_SET(1, 3, 3)</ref>)&gt;; }; gpio-consumer { out-gpios = &lt;&amp;port8 2 (GPIO_PULL_UP | <ref refid="renesas-rz-gpio_8h_1a6916bb2358989ef5498e1c87209dd995" kindref="member">RZ_GPIO_IOLH_SET(2)</ref>)&gt;; }; </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
